  "descriptions": [
    {
      "text": "パルスマンはサイバー犯罪と戦うために作られた電気のヒーローです。7つのステージにわたる約50のレベルでギャラクシーギャングと戦いましょう。パルスマンは、ゲームプレイの面で『ソニック・ザ・ヘッジホッグ』と『ロックマン』の融合として最もよく表現されます。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "romu"
    },
    {
      "text": "Pulseman is a platform game only released on cartridge for a Japanese audience, but was available to North American consumers via the Sega Channel. The game was not sold in Europe.\n\nIt was developed by Game Freak, the development team that would later go on to produce the Pokémon series of games for Nintendo. Many of Pulseman's staff, including director Ken Sugimori and composer Junichi Masuda worked on both games.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "igdb"
    },
